What:		/sys/class/st54spi/st54spi/device/st54spi_power_state_snap
Date:		Oct 2024
KernelVersion:  6.6
Contact:	"George Chang" <georgekgchang@google.com>
Description:
		For collecting power state transition data, userspace can
		request a snapshot of current power record via reading
		"st54spi_power_state_snap" sysfs.
		And it returns current system timestamp of the last snapshot.
		After requesting a snapshot, userspace can read the power
		records from the following sysfs.
		st54spi_power_idle_count
		st54spi_power_idle_duration
		st54spi_power_idle_entry_time
		st54spi_power_idle_exit_time
		st54spi_power_active_count
		st54spi_power_active_duration
		st54spi_power_active_entry_time
		st54spi_power_active_exit_time
		st54spi_power_snap_time
Users:		eSE HAL and Power record collection process in userspace.

